    differentiationNotes: `Struggling learners benefit from explaining that pirates sailed along colonial trade routes to intercept ships carrying valuable cargo and dividing treasure among a crew using division, such as if sixty gold coins are shared equally among twelve crew members, each receives five coins \u2014 and calculating how far a ship travels using multiplication, such as a ship sailing at eight knots for five hours covering forty nautical miles. Advanced learners benefit from analyzing how economic conditions after European wars created the Golden Age of Piracy, explaining that thousands of trained sailors lost their naval employment and turned to piracy as colonial trade routes offered rich targets \u2014 and writing a multi-paragraph report explaining celestial navigation with the mathematics of dead reckoning, describing how latitude was determined from the North Star\u2019s angle above the horizon and how speed was measured using knotted ropes dropped overboard, with calculations of ship travel distance using speed times time.`,
