    differentiationNotes: `Struggling learners benefit from explaining the sense-think-act cycle using a simple example like a robot vacuum that senses a wall (bump sensor detects an obstacle), decides to turn (the processor follows a rule: if obstacle detected, turn right), and changes direction (the motor actuator drives the wheels to turn) \u2014 and calculating how far a robot travels using multiplication, such as a robot moving at ten centimeters per second for thirty seconds covering three hundred centimeters or three meters. Advanced learners benefit from analyzing how different sensor types work together in complex robots, explaining how a self-driving car uses cameras for visual recognition, lidar for precise distance mapping, and radar for detecting other vehicles\u2019 speed simultaneously \u2014 and writing a multi-paragraph report explaining how conditional logic and loops enable robots to make decisions and repeat tasks, with examples of if-then-else statements that sort objects by color and counting loops that repeat assembly steps a precise number of times.`,
    parentTakeaway: `Robots as engineering \u2014 identify the sense-think-act cycle in household devices like automatic doors (motion sensor detects approach, controller decides to open, motor opens door), robotic vacuums (bump and infrared sensors detect obstacles, processor plans cleaning path, motors drive wheels and brushes), and smart speakers (microphone senses voice, processor interprets speech, speaker produces response); discuss how programming gives robots step-by-step instructions with decision points, where if-then-else logic lets robots choose different actions based on sensor data; calculate robot movement problems using multiplication, such as a robot moving at twelve centimeters per second for forty-five seconds covering five hundred forty centimeters; explore the history of automation from ancient mechanical curiosities to modern factory robots and AI assistants; discuss how robots are used in factories, hospitals, space exploration, search and rescue, and everyday life.`,
